
Ranger Help for: history
========================

SUMMARY:    
The Ranger is a woodsman, fighter, tracker, rogue, and limited magic user
all rolled into one. His abilities in the wilderness are unmatched. Able to survive in the harshest of conditions, Nature is his friend..sharing a special akindship to it with Druids. He has the strength of a fighter
and the cunning of a thief. More often than not, the Ranger prefers to fight alone, though not always true. 

The Ranger's origins can be traced to the times when settlements were less developed, when a warrior had to rely on his smarts and the land. This relationship brought about a love of nature and an afinity for protecting it. 
Using all at his disposal and living off of the land makes the Ranger a very tough, stout character. He might use the land to his advantage in fights, or to locate lost explorers.

Since the roots of a Ranger lie mostly in his growing up in a natural setting, only certain guilds may meld with the views of a Ranger and only after a long time. Rangers prefer solitude, and only later in their lives(higher lev) might they want explore other guilds.

There are a many different Rangers, yet all are linked to nature, some are more affluent in certain areas than others, but all recognize the uses of their surroundings. Rangers in their birth terrain(primary) have certain advantages over there opponents or may have other skills/spells available to them. Most Rangers also 'know' a secondary terrain that may help them in their adventures. 

Lastly, Rangers being the master of nature and all within it, on rare occasions may call on nature itself to help them. With the help of Gaeia,
Ranger can sometimes perform minor magics to aid them in combat or
exploring. These take a lot out of Rangers, since they not performed
on a regular basis.

=============================================================================
